"title": "2378: kingdom of God, characteristics of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2378: kingdom of god, characteristics of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Those who have entered the kingdom must live according to its values, anticipating the reign of peace which will come when Jesus Christ returns.</p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God does not conform to the standards of this world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:36\">JHN 18:36</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Those who inherit the kingdom of God are to bear its fruit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34-Matt25:36\">MAT 25:34–25:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:10-2Pet1:11\">2PE 1:10–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God is and will be a kingdom of peace</h2>\n<h3>Peace between people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:4\">MIC 4:1–4:4</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:18\">JAS 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:5\">ISA 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:24-Isa19:25\">ISA 19:24–19:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:4-Mic5:5\">MIC 5:4–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:9\">MAT 5:9</a> <em>The Sermon on the Mount (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:1-Matt7:29\">Mt 5:1–7:29</a>) is often thought of as a description of life in the kingdom.</em></p>\n<h3>The peace and prosperity of all creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:6-Isa11:9\">ISA 11:6–11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:1-Isa35:2\">ISA 35:1–35:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:9\">ISA 35:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:17-Isa41:19\">ISA 41:17–41:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:9\">EZK 47:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:12\">EZK 47:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:21-Hos2:22\">HOS 2:21–2:22</a></p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God is a kingdom of forgiveness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:3-Luke17:4\">LUK 17:3–17:4</a></p>\n<h2>Status in the kingdom of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:1-Matt18:5\">MAT 18:1–18:5</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:33-Mark9:37\">MRK 9:33–9:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:46-Luke9:48\">LUK 9:46–9:48</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:25–20:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:25-Luke22:27\">LUK 22:25–22:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:19\">MAT 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:11\">MAT 11:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:28\">LUK 7:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:30\">MAT 19:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:31\">MRK 10:31</a></p>",
